In recent years technology for consumer use has greatly advanced. Devices have been created to add ease of everyday tasks and connect them throughout aspects of people's lives. Smart Homes are where technology is heading. The idea of a Smart Home or smart room is to provide personalization, security, accessibility, and increase functionality of the devices used in homes. Along with personalization of the room, the smart room can also save on energy usage. This paper will present a system designed for a room using a Raspberry Pi module along with interchangeable and customizable sensors to allow full control and personalization of any room in a building. As well as controlling the room using IoT a database of information like a log of occupants, time occupied, and room conditions.
